{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἐξαρκ-έω</b>, <br /> <br /><Level2><b>__I</b></Level2> of objects, <b>to be quite enough for, suffice for,</b> τινί [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.AD(?): Heraclitus 114, 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Coloneus” 6, 1116, “Ph.” 459, etc.; ἔμοιγ᾽ ἐ. ὃς ἂν μὴ κακὸς ᾖ 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Protagoras” 346c; ὁ βίος μοι δοκεῖ τῷ μήκει τοῦ λόγου οὐκ ἐξαρκεῖν [prev. author] “Phd.” 108d; ἐ. εἴς τι 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 19.55, 30.20; πρός τι 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 526d, 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Memorabilia” 4.1.5 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: with <i>infinitive</i>, μία μεσότης ἂν ἐξήρκει.. συνδεῖν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Timaeus” 32a \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>absolutely</i>, <b>suffice,</b> μέτρια δ᾽ ἐξαρκεῖν ἔφη [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Supplices” 866, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Andocides Orator 4.15; βραχὺς.. ἐξήρκει λόγος 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 18.196. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__I.2</b></Level3> <i>impersonal</i>, ἐξαρκεῖ <b>it is enough for, suffices for,</b> with <i>dative</i> <i>person</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Protagoras” 336c, +others\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: with <i>infinitive</i> added, ἐ. ἡμῖν ἡσυχίην ἄγειν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 7.161; ἐ. σώματι εἶναι σώματι 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 341e; also ἐξαρκέσει σοι τύραννον γενέσθαι [prev. author] Alcaeus2.141a; ἐξαρκέσει εἰπεῖν 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 27.12; οὐκ ἐξαρκεῖ περὶ τούτου μόνον αὐτῷ ψεύσασθαι 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 3.25, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 19.47 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: with <i>dative</i> <i>person</i> et <i>participle</i>, ταῦτα ἔχουσιν οὐκ ἐξήρκεσεν αὐτοῖς [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 47.52: _absolutely_, οὐκ ἂν ἐξαρκέσειεν [prev. author] 21.129; ἐξαρκεῖ \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<b>enough!</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Gorgias” 503a, “Hp.Ma.” 302b; ὡς ἐξαρκέσαν, εἰ.. 4th c.BC: Isaeus Orator 6.13. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> of the subject, <b>to be satisfied</b> or <b>content with,</b> κτεάτεσσι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “O.” 5.24 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἐ. διαίτῃ <b>to be strong enough</b> for it, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “ἀφορισμοί” 1.9 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; πᾶσιν ἐ. <b>to be a match</b> for all, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Supplices” 574: _absolutely_, ἐξαρκέσας ἦν Ζεύς\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] Zeus was <b>strong enough,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"[prev. work] 511: with \">Refs</a>]<i>participle</i>, τὸν νοῦν διδάσκαλον ἔχουσα ἐξήρκουν ἐμοί I <b>contented myself, was satisfied</b> with having, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Tr.” 653, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Equites” 524 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; πῶς ἂν.. ἐξαρκέσειε.. ἐκτίνω; how <b>could</b> he pay <b>enough?</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Hiero” 7.12:\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] —<i>passive</i>, οὐκ ἐξηρκεῖτο φυγαδεύειν uncertain reading in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 13.6.6. \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> <b>assist, succour,</b> φίλοις [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “N.” 1.32: with _accusative_, ταῦτα ὁ φίλος πρὸ τοῦ φίλου ἐξήρκεσεν 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Memorabilia” 2.4.7. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G7301","accentedUnicode":"ἐξαρκέω","shortDef":"be enough","mediumDef":"be enough","stepGloss":"be enough","stepTransliteration":"exarkeō","count":0,"_step_Type":"verb"}]}